-- CSI 300 Index May Rise to 4,300 Next Year, Goldman Sachs Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-01T02:27:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-01/csi-300-index-may-rise-to-4-300-next-year-gaining-27-goldman-sachs-says.html
China’s CSI 300 Index, representing
the 300 biggest companies in the country, may rise to 4,300 by
next year, according to Goldman Sachs Group Inc. The forecast
represents a 27 percent gain from the Oct. 29 closing level.  The Hang Seng China Enterprises Index may climb to 16,500
in 2011, Goldman Sachs analysts Helen Zhu, Ben Bei, Timothy Moe
and Kinger Lau, wrote in a note to clients. The analysts also
upgraded banks and transport stocks to “overweight” from
“neutral,” while cutting consumer staples producers to
“neutral” from “overweight” and utilities to “underweight”
from “neutral.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Allen Wan at 
 awan3@bloomberg.net  